Class ForkJoinSolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.ForkJoinTask<V>
      • java.util.concurrent.RecursiveTask<java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>>
        • amazed.solver.SequentialSolver
          • amazed.solver.ForkJoinSolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.concurrent.Future<java.util.List<java.lang.Integer>>

    public class ForkJoinSolver
extends SequentialSolver
    ForkJoinSolver implements a solver for Maze objects using a fork/join multi-thread depth-first search.

    Instances of ForkJoinSolver should be run by a ForkJoinPool object.

      • ForkJoinSolver

        public ForkJoinSolver(Maze maze,
                      int forkAfter)
        Creates a solver that searches in maze from the start node to a goal, forking after a given number of visited nodes.
        Parameters:
        maze - the maze to be searched
        forkAfter - the number of steps (visited nodes) after which a parallel task is forked; if forkAfter <= 0 the solver never forks new tasks

    • Method Detail

      • compute

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> compute()
        Searches for and returns the path, as a list of node identifiers, that goes from the start node to a goal node in the maze. If such a path cannot be found (because there are no goals, or all goals are unreacheable), the method returns null.
        Overrides:
        compute in class SequentialSolver
        Returns:
        the list of node identifiers from the start node to a goal node in the maze; null if such a path cannot be found.
